  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      For the purpose of assessing the spread of the local anaesthetic after injecting it between
      abdominal muscles on both sides, the investigators will test if the patient can feel a change
      in the perception of cold and warm, as well as being pricked with a blunt needle. The
      investigators will also take several blood samples, together with routine samples, to measure
      the concentration of the local anesthetic in the blood.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
